      <section>
        <h3><a id="what_is" class="anchor" href="#what_is" aria-hidden="true"><span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>What is BeAPI&#8482; API Framework?</h3>

<p>The <b>BeAPI&#8482; API Framework</b> is a Plugin for <a href="https://grails.org/">Grails</a> on the <a href="http://projects.spring.io/spring-boot/">Spring Boot Microservice</a>.</p>
<p>It installs a full microservice API Framework allowing improved automation, code reduction, simplified/fast development, and improved performance/scalability for distributed architectures.</p>
<p>It was built by <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/orubel">a leader in the API industry</a> who has spent years solving issues with API installations in distributed architectures and who has advised/consulted/worked with enterprise leaders such as Apple, Netflix, VMWare, Cisco, Mashery, Amazon and others.</p>

<h3>
<a id="benefits" class="anchor" href="#benefits" aria-hidden="true"><span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>What Are It's Benefits?</h3>

<p>The <b>BeAPI&#8482; API Framework</b> is based upon the principles of <a href="http://www.infoq.com/author/Owen-Rubel">API abstraction and shared IO state</a>. These create an entirely <b>NEW API Pattern</b> allowing us the ability to do the following:</p>
<ul>
<li><b>60-80% code reduction for API development</b></li>
<li><b>Vastly simplified API development</b></li>
<li><b>Faster & More scalable</b></li>
<li>On-the-fly reloading of endpoint data (no shutting down server to make changes)</li>
<li>Ability to sychronize endpoint data across all services</li>
</ul>
<p>In addition, it also has the following built-in functionality...</p>
<li>CORS</li>
<li>Rate Limiting</li>
<li>Token Validation</li>
<li>Automated Webhooks</li>
<li>Automated Api docs</li>
<li>Automated Role check</li>
<li>Automated Batching</li>
<li>API Chaining</li>
<li>Reduction in dropped threads</li>
<li>100% stateless</li>
<li>Parallelized Functionality</li>
</ul>

<h3>
<a id="apidev" class="anchor" href="#apidev" aria-hidden="true"><span aria-hidden="true" class="octicon octicon-link"></span></a>Easy API Development</h3>

<p>All communication logic and data are abstracted away from the controllers and services leaving the controllers to only deal with retrieving and returning a resource. This makes API development INCREDIBLY simple and FAST. You simply have to:</p>
<ul>
<li>Install the plugin</li>
<li>Build a JSON IO State file for each controller</li>
</ul>

<p>There are <b>NO ANNOTATIONS</b> to be set, <b>NO SERVICES</b> to rely upon, <b>NO CHECKS</b> to be made. The IO State file acts as a properties file for endpoint rules for ALL services in your architectures and is handled at the communication layer... NOT at the business logic. This makes it faster and more scalable and reduces code needed to create API's.</p>

